newsitem.title: USA: CBOT soymeal seen up $0.50 to $1.00 on exports.
newsitem.headline: CBOT soymeal seen up $0.50 to $1.00 on exports.

text.p: CBOT soymeal futures were expected to open $0.50 to $1.00 per ton higher on brisk weekly exports, and soyoil is seen 0.05 to 0.10 cent per lb lower, traders said.
USDA put soymeal sales at 97,000 tonnes. That figure came in above trade expectations for 60,000 to 80,000 tonnes.
Soyoil sales were a paltry 5,100 tonnes, so traders were looking for soymeal/soyoil spreading during Thursday's trade.
Citing high prices, traders in China dismissed Wednesday's talk of a recent purchase of U.S. soymeal.
